text: it s dark ,grey and too unpredictable no one is spared here virtually it rips every aspect of modern American reality apart as ugly vicious and corrupt ,the law enforcement is as bad as the mafia mob here ,the mafia itself is white Russian jewish who operate from Moscow to tel aviv through Kosher meat business in Atlanta ¬†that is used to obliterate all opposition in the garb of religion .I was fascinated by the detailed direction where no one is likeable or adorable but just human struggling with that greedy streak embedded within .I think it has stereotypes so it will not be ground breaking as corrupt cops and jewish mafia has been discussed before on screen but when it mixes the whole equation with the American black race and how the races interact there ,we are treading new ground the kate winslet jewish wife character and how she describes Russian jews and Ejiofor as a corrupt black Atlanta cop who is father of a jewish black child might well be the best two if not the most innovative characters American cinema invented¬† in this decade they do and say things which left me tingling with horror and ecstasy as nothing is sacred or holy when it comes to their self¬†interests and hillcoat does not glorify anyone just observes non chalantly and lets the audience decide and woody harrelson is the system who is an enigma here and possibly the only one in control and the clue to whole charade of corruption as the camera suggests ,the direction is so detailed and precise it makes innaritu look like a juvenile as every frame almost explodes with details of American slums suburbs gun battles mob massacres and black predicament and its simply riveting despite its complex narrative which some will find hard to digest
